item.title: Delta and Other servers [317s]
item.dc:creator: @bryanc Bryanc
item.description:
@bryanc wrote:

No, just because Runescape private servers are intended to be like Runescape itself doesn’t mean you should half ass something.

Look at it like this: If you were to create a wL based server, or Delta in this case (either because they both suck) you will learn Java yes. But you will have the mindset that the way things are done in the servers are the correct way to go about things in other programs. Therefore causing a greater issue being you are going to spread shit. They will now all take this knowledge of wL, Delta, etc. based servers and go teach others more shit and you got yourself a chain reaction.

If people were to actually learn Java, then try and create a private server we wouldn’t be stuck in this rut of horrible methods of doing things. So don’t say Delta isn’t bad, because Delta sucks just like winterLove.

Read full topic

Anyway, button clicking is in clickingMost.java, and the ffirst item click is handled in Potions.java.
